Java supports several built in data types:
1.Numeric data type(int,float,double)
2.Character->char
3.boolean->boolean
4.Reference=>Array,objects,class

5000->
1000->






Java supports a variety of data types for reprsenting the values in program.
1byte->8 bit
1.primitive Data types
byte->8-bit signed integer
short->16-bit(2 byte)
int->32-bit(4 byte)
long->64-bit(8 byte)
float->32-bit(4 byte)
double->64-bit(8-byte)
char-16-bit(2-byte)->'10'
boolean=>true or false
2.Reference Data types
Object=>the base class of all the classses in java is Object class 
String=>String represent a sequence of characters.
Array =>Collection of values with same type.
Class->A use-defined typed in java.https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/datatypes.html#:~:text=byte%3A%20The%20byte%20data%20type,value%20of%20127%20(inclusive).




